{"title":"Bicycle Portage Handles: A Simple Design with a Big Story","link":"https://theradavist.com/bicycle-portage-handles-a-simple-design-with-a-big-story/","date":1689709223000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Brian-and-His-Rare-Earth-Cycle-Craft-Tour-Divide-Bike-60.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Brian-and-His-Rare-Earth-Cycle-Craft-Tour-Divide-Bike-60.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Brian-and-His-Rare-Earth-Cycle-Craft-Tour-Divide-Bike-60.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Brian-and-His-Rare-Earth-Cycle-Craft-Tour-Divide-Bike-60.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Brian-and-His-Rare-Earth-Cycle-Craft-Tour-Divide-Bike-60.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Brian-and-His-Rare-Earth-Cycle-Craft-Tour-Divide-Bike-60.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Brian-and-His-Rare-Earth-Cycle-Craft-Tour-Divide-Bike-60.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Brian-and-His-Rare-Earth-Cycle-Craft-Tour-Divide-Bike-60.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Today we featured <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/rare-earth-cycle-craft-touring-bike-review/\" target=\"_blank\">Brian’s Rare Earth Cycles touring bike</a>, which featured a portage handle. This detail has resulted in a good deal of internet chatter, lauding this simple design as a clever detail for touring bikes. Brian credits Meriwether Cycles’ work for inspiring him to include one on his bike, yet Meriwether was inspired by other framebuilders of the past like <a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/adventurecycling/4110608282\" target=\"_blank\">Sam Braxton</a>.</p>\n<p>While this simple bit of tubing looks pretty straightforward, there’s a big backstory behind its use. Roll on over to <a href=\"https://meriwethercycles.com/2021/07/08/the-portage-handle/\" target=\"_blank\">Meriwether Cycles</a>‘ blog to read all about it!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/bicycle-portage-handles-a-simple-design-with-a-big-story/\">Bicycle Portage Handles: A Simple Design with a Big Story</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"a4dc13270ae3a03ef26af36b2c51eeeb445821fd49ce1b8b78e766e5bd48e395","category":"Cycling"}